text=(:if authgroup @tas:)%0a%0a(:toggle id=gi show="show grading interface" hide="hide grading interface":)%0a%0a>>id=gi%3c%3c%0a%0a[[GradebookArticles.{$Name}|See article in gradebook]] \\%0a[[{$FullName}?action=diff|See all changes to article]]%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradeitem:)%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradingcomment:)%0a%0a>>%3c%3c%0a%0a----%0a%0a(:ifend:)%0a%0a[[!LinguisticDiscriminationInTheWild]]%0a%0a!Speaking Korean with a Foreign Accent%0a%0a:Author: evelynC%0a%0a'''Summary:''' \\%0a%0a[[#summary]]%0a%0aThe article discusses the negative reactions foreigners receive when they speak Korean with a foreign accent.%0a%0a[[#summaryends]]%0a%0a----%0a[[#content]]%0a%0aArticle: http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20200712000114%0a%0aThis article discusses the negative reactions that foreigners receive when they speak Korean with an accent. As Korea is a homogenous nation with mainly Koreans, there is a lack of diversity when compared to a country such as America. Therefore, they are not as used to foreign accents and view them in a negative manner. Some characteristics of a foreign Korean accent include not being able to pronounce tense and aspirated consonants.%0a%0aThe article specifically follows K-Pop artists or entertainers in the industry that are not native Koreans. Many of these people are subject to criticism when speaking Korean, not their first language, with an accent. Mispronunciation and accents are made fun of by Korean variety show hosts, reporters, and the general public. Especially those of older generations partake in mockery of foreign accents.%0a%0aWhen mockery occurs on such a large scale, it makes foreigners unmotivated or afraid to speak Korean. The article discusses how many public figures such as K-pop stars that are not native Koreans have a fear of speaking on reality TV shows because of the negative reactions their accent would receive.%0a%0a[[#contentends]]%0a----%0a----%0a%0a!!Expansions:%0a[[#expansions]]%0a%0a[